<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-20T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="579" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3069: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-20T13:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            20, 1920—1 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>344. Your 290 [<hi rend="italic">390</hi>], November 19, 8 p.m.</p>
                            <p>You should limit your communication to the Chinese Government to a
                                mere statement of the Government’s approval of the Consortium
                                Agreement, using such parts of text of public announcement mentioned
                                in Department’s 336, November 16, 7 p.m., as may be deemed
                                appropriate.</p>
                            <p>Department is giving announcement to Press today. American Group at
                                New York gave to Press a summary of Consortium Agreement which has
                                appeared in this morning’s papers.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>